---
source: crates/loom/tests/cli_help.rs
assertion_line: 173
expression: "loom_help(&[\"loop\"])"
---
Execute task beads from explicit work roots or the active work epic

Usage: loom loop [OPTIONS] [BEAD_OR_EPIC_ID]...

Arguments:
  [BEAD_OR_EPIC_ID]...  Bead or epic ids to run; omitted means the sole open `loom:active` epic

Options:
  -p, --parallel <PARALLEL>  Concurrent dispatch slots (`-p N` / `--parallel N`). Default 1 [default: 1]
  -w, --workspace <PATH>     Workspace root. Defaults to the current working directory
  -A, --agent <BACKEND>      Override the agent backend for this invocation [possible values: claude, pi, direct]
      --profile <PROFILE>    Override the per-bead `profile:X` label resolution
      --host-key             Explicitly allow ambient host Git credentials and signing config
      --plain                ASCII output, no color, no OSC 8. Pipe-safe. Implied when stdout is not a TTY or `NO_COLOR` is set. Mutually exclusive with `--json` and `--raw`
      --json                 Emit one pretty-printed JSON object per line on stdout. Mutually exclusive with `--plain` and `--raw`
      --raw                  Emit one compact JSON line per event on stdout — same as the on-disk JSONL shape. Mutually exclusive with `--plain`, `--json`, and `-v/--verbose`
  -v, --verbose              Add diagnostic event metadata to human rendering
      --trace                Mirror raw Rust tracing diagnostics to stderr
  -h, --help                 Print help
